EASTERN CAPE - President Cyril Ramaphosa has hit out at critics of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. He says she must be remembered as someone who always fought for what was right. WATCH: Mbeki on Winnie's legacy Ramaphosa was delivering a eulogy at Madikizela-Mandela's memorial service in her home village in Mbizana, Eastern Cape. "If there was anything mam' Winnie hated was corruption and this demon that has come called state corruption and state capture. I am making this point about Winnie being a product of a time because there are some who have sought to demonise her character even in death," he said. Madikizela-Mandela will be laid to rest this weekend on 14 April. eNCA